parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ABS
VSC
and TRAC lights illuminate on the dashboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
the brakes make a grinding noise
or the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warping of the front brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when braking, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
the brake rotors need to be replaced frequently
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates when pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake disintegrates into a pile of parts
the parking brake does not engage properly
the vehicle rolls or moves unintentionally when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds or on slippery roads.
symptoms: The VSC (Vehicle Stability Control) and TRAC (Traction Control) lights illuminate on the dashboard
the brake light comes on
and the vehicle may experience sudden acceleration or deceleration
loss of traction
or unusual braking behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, skid, or lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The VSC
TRAC
and ABS lights on the dashboard illuminate
the vehicle slows down or decelerates suddenly
the brakes grind or make a noise
the vehicle pulls to one side
loss of power or acceleration
and unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust holes in the frame
excessive corrosion
frame fracture
loss of structural rigidity
and compromised safety in the event of a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Toyota to properly address the frame rust and corrosion issue through recalls and repairs can lead to continued safety risks for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Lack of notification about recalls
inadequate repair solutions
and refusal to take responsibility for the safety issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of transparency and communication from Toyota about the frame rust and corrosion issue can lead to vehicle owners being unaware of the safety risks and not taking necessary precautions.
symptoms: Failure to notify owners about recalls
lack of information about the safety issue
and inadequate communication about repair solutions.
